Executive Profile
Mary T. Szela  Chief Executive Officer and Director, Novelion Therapeutics Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships54$7,410,556As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Ms. Mary T. Szela has been the Chief Executive Officer of Novelion Therapeutics Inc. since November 29, 2016. Ms. Szel served as the Chief Executive Officer of Aegerion Pharmaceuticals, Inc. from January 07, 2016 to November 29, 2016. Ms. Szela served as the Chief Executive Officer of Melinta Therapeutics, Inc. from April 3, 2013 to August 2015, Chairperson since January 4, 2013 and also served as its President. Ms. Szela served as a Senior Vice President of Global Strategic ... Marketing and Services at Abbott Diabetes Care, Inc. since January 2010. Ms. Szela served as a Senior Vice President of Global Strategic Marketing and Services Pharmaceutical Products Group at Abbott Laboratories since 2010 and also served as its Senior Vice President of U S Pharmaceuticals from 2008 to 2009. She served more than two decades in senior roles at Abbott Laboratories. She served as Senior Vice President, U.S. Pharmaceuticals. at Abbott Diabetes Care, Inc. She served as Senior Vice President of Pharmaceutical Operations of Abbott's commercial pharmaceutical business in the United States from August 2007 to 2008. She served as Corporate Officer at Abbott Laboratories since 2001. She served as Vice President of Commercial Pharmaceutical Operations at Abbott Laboratories since 2006, where she was responsible for sales and marketing of many of Abbott's pharmaceutical brands, including HUMIRA. She served as Vice President of Pharmaceutical Products, Primary Care Operations of Abbott Laboratories from 2001 to 2006. She joined Abbott in 1987 and has held several leadership positions at Abbott, including Divisional Vice President of Hospital Products Business Sector from 1998 to 2001. She served as General Manager of Anesthesia, Hospital Products since 1998. She worked for the University of Illinois Hospital. She served as the Chairperson of Rib-X Pharmaceuticals, Inc. since January 4, 2013 and has been its Director since January 4, 2013. She has been a Director of Novelion Therapeutics Inc. since November 29, 2016. She has been a Director of Coherus Biosciences, Inc. since July 2014. She has been a Director at Aegerion Pharmaceuticals, Inc., since January 07, 2016. She has been Director of Arisaph Pharmaceuticals, Inc. since 2007. She serves as a Director of Suneva Medical, Inc. She served as Director of Novo Nordisk A/S from March 19, 2015 to May 16, 2017. She served as a Director of Melinta Therapeutics, Inc. since January 4, 2013. She served as a Director of Receptos, Inc. from July 2014 to August 27, 2015. Ms. Szela earned a Bachelor's degree in Nursing in 1985 and a Master's degree in Business Administration in 1991 from the University of Illinois.Read Full Background




